    • rotateBy

      public Force2d rotateBy(edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Rotation2d angle)
      Applies a rotation to the force in 2d space.

      This multiplies the force vector by a counterclockwise rotation matrix of the given angle. [x_new] [other.cos, -other.sin][x] [y_new] = [other.sin, other.cos][y]

      For example, rotating a Force2d of {2, 0} by 90 degrees will return a Force2d of {0, 2}.

      Parameters:
      angle - The rotation to rotate the force by.
      Returns:
      The new rotated force.

    • plus

      public Force2d plus(Force2d other)
      Adds two forces in 2d space and returns the sum. This is similar to vector addition.

      For example, Force2d{1.0, 2.5} + Force2d{2.0, 5.5} = Force2d{3.0, 8.0}

      Parameters:
      other - The force to add.
      Returns:
      The sum of the forces.

    • minus

      public Force2d minus(Force2d other)
      Subtracts the other force from the other force and returns the difference.

      For example, Force2d{5.0, 4.0} - Force2d{1.0, 2.0} = Force2d{4.0, 2.0}

      Parameters:
      other - The force to subtract.
      Returns:
      The difference between the two forces.

    • unaryMinus

      public Force2d unaryMinus()

      Returns:
